just a dude with a camera trying to capture all the beautiful things this world has to offer.📸
Well…2022 was certainly a wild year for me. Never have I laughed as much or cried as hard as I did this year. I ended up losing what I wanted most, but gained what I needed more, and learned valuable lessons through it all. I fully believe I grew more in 2022 than I ever have in my entire life altogether. Though I hit rock bottom, I eventually bounced back up, and now I’m soaring higher than ever. Life is good, God is great, and I mean it when I say I have never been happier. With some incredible opportunities awaiting, and wild plans already being set into motion, 2023 is looking bright, and I dare say, might end up being the best year of my entire life. I love you, thank you for loving me too❤️

i truly found who i am this year, and i’ve never been more at peace in my entire life. friends, family, society—even your own mirror, will try to categorize and label you, but once you find the Truth, you’ll never doubt who you are again. this is the message of my new short film, and i cannot wait to share it with you next week❤️

Too many emotions behind this film for me to fit into a single caption. I just want you to know it is the single most proudest thing I have ever made in my entire life, and definitely the most exhausting. I’ve had this vision in my head for a decade, and I’m extremely grateful to the humans who helped me bring it into existence. It’s kinda cringe to say but I’ve weeped multiple times watching the final result, and I pray it touches your heart as much as it ironically did my own. See you on January 1st🙏🏽💙

on this day, eight years ago, God brought someone into my life who would completely change it, definitely challenge it, and make me a much better human than i was before. today i’m celebrating eight years of brotherhood with @jaredherzogmusic, and though it’s been a rollercoaster of a ride, i quite honestly can’t remember life without you in it, i don’t think anyone in our families can (and idk if that’s a good thing or a bad thing😅). thanks for being the bestest friend i could ever and will ever have. #FoyZogAdventures

this is a final thank you to the beautiful humans who opened their hearts, let me capture their life on camera, and allowed me to share these stories with the world. what a wonderful life being able to do what i love, making friends with the most incredible people along the way, all the while creating films that inspire others. like honestly, how lucky am i?🥹🖤
